snippet.title: I Saw What I Saw | arr. Susan LaBarr
snippet.description:
I Saw What I Saw arranged for SSA voices with piano and optional cello by Susan LaBarr. 

"Your courage asks me what I'm afraid of and what I know of love." This piece by singer-songwriter Sara Groves, written after a trip to help people in need in a third-world country, deeply expresses ideas of empathy. Arranged for three-part treble voices with piano and optional cello, this setting is timely for treble choirs of all ages.

Purchase the music: https://giamusic.com/resource/i-saw-what-i-saw-printed-music-ww2126
